{
  "stem": "8842.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By that time, my wooden sandals fell apart completely, and I was actually walking barefoot in the snow.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it's hard to describe the pain walking around that way.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The worse part-- worse than that was yet that we didn't have water to wash, and we didn't wash for weeks and months by now.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- I'm going to say something terrible-- we were all covered with lice, and the pain of that was probably worse than the cold, what lice can do to you.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We tried to wash our heads to get rid of the lice.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Believe it or not, in-- with the hot water that we had wasn't even so hot, so the five girls that we've been together, we shared each-- with each other the water one day, and one used to wash her hair out.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The second day, I used to give mine to the other girl.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so during the week, each one of us had a chance to wash once at least a week our hair.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But then of course it didn't help because we didn't have soap.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was just no, no help to us at all.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "When it got very, very bitter cold, they finally took us out from those tents, and they brought us into a place what used to be a mill-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] flour mill-- and they made those wooden places that we could sleep together, just some plain wood.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was nothing else, not a blanket or, God forbid, anything, not at all, just lay there on the wood.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But at least we were warm, close, our bodies next to each other, and we were not as freezing as in those tents.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
